cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. The use of neural networks and machine learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of structured transition matrices, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of a conditional optimal selector suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
